org.cougaar.planning.ldm.policy
Interface RuleParameter

All Superinterfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable
All Known Implementing Classes:
BooleanRuleParameter, ClassRuleParameter, DoubleRuleParameter, EnumerationRuleParameter, IntegerRuleParameter, KeyRuleParameter, LongRuleParameter, PredicateRuleParameter, RangeRuleParameter, StringRuleParameter
public interface RuleParameter
extends java.lang.Cloneable

A RuleParameter is generic object containing a parameter value Values may be one of several types: INTEGER - Integer value type (within given bounds) DOUBLE - Double value type (within given bounds) STRING - String value type LONG - Long value type (within given bounds) ENUMERATION - Enumeration value type (String from given list) BOOLEAN - Boolean value type CLASS - Java class value type (implementing given interface) KEY - Set of String values (with default) indexed off a key RANGE - Set of values (String or RuleParameter) (with default) indexed from a list of integer ranges
